WEBVTT

00:00:00.320 --> 00:00:05.920
Two AI products. They're built on top of the same base model, so they must be the same, right?

00:00:05.920 --> 00:00:11.360
Well, not exactly. AI products may be built on the same base model, but the product developers

00:00:11.360 --> 00:00:17.120
decide what instructions they get and what tools they have access to, and tools are where the magic

00:00:17.120 --> 00:00:23.680
happens. Because at its core, an LLM alone is just text in and text out. It can write you Python code,

00:00:23.680 --> 00:00:29.840
but by itself it doesn't have any way to run that Python code. It's just text. A tool is sort

00:00:29.840 --> 00:00:35.680
of like a predefined function that the model is allowed to request, and using the tool, the LLM

00:00:35.680 --> 00:00:41.520
might say something like, hey, I want to run this Python code, and then an application like Positron

00:00:41.520 --> 00:00:47.119
goes and runs it and hands the results back to the LLM. Again, the LLM is just taking text in

00:00:47.119 --> 00:00:52.160
and outputting more text. So when one AI product can, say, browse the internet for you and another

00:00:52.160 --> 00:00:57.840
one can't, even though it has the same access to the same underlying model, it's because they have

00:00:57.840 --> 00:00:58.880
different tools.

